+ Comparing Approaches
++ Row & Column Security
+++_ Fewer objects (table + functions)
+++_ Enforcement at source
+++_ Supports read/write patterns
+++_ Limited to single table
++ Dynamic Views
+++_ More objects to manage
+++_ Multi-table composition
+++_ Read-only (typically)
+++_ Decoupled from storage design
-- Key trade-off
---_ Simplicity vs. abstraction
---_ Default: Row & Column Security
---_ Exception: multi-table or strict isolation
@endmindmap
